<tr><td bgcolor="#3F403F" width="98%" class="cheader">Board games - tell me some good ones</td><td bgcolor="3F403F" valign="top" align="right" width="22"><img src="/swtcg/gfx/theme1/topcorner.gif" width="23" height="22" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="right"></td></tr>
<tr><td width="98%" colspan=2><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" class="cbody">
<tr><td><font class="bfont"> From: Lt. Cabbage</font><BR><font class="bfont"><A HREF='/swtcg/resources/buzz.php'>Back to Topics List</A></font><BR><font class="bfont"><A HREF='#postarea'>Jump to Post Area</A></font><BR><font class="bfont"><A HREF='/swtcg/resources/buzz.php?id=8524'><b>REFRESH THIS TOPIC</b></A></font><TABLE WIDTH='100%' border=0 cellpadding=6><tr><td width='4' bgcolor=#CCCCCC>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><font class="h2font"> Name</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><font class="h2font"> Comment</td></tr><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Patrick M. S</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF' ><font class="bfont">sounds like fun. Considering that in Caylus, Sara gets all mad at me when I use the Provost against her, this might be a tough one to play with her :( <br><BR><font size=1>12:36 12-05-2007</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#CCCCCC>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><font class="bfont"><B>Shewski</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#CCCCCC' ><font class="bfont">The game takes about 2.5 hrs vs an equal opponent.  I got lucky and won one in 1.5 but that was early on before we got better.<br />
<br />
One player is USSR, one USA.  It covers the cold war and in split into three sections, early, mid and late war.  <br />
<br />
Your actions are card driven.  Each card has a point value and game text.  YOu can use a card for either... but if you use a card with opponent&#39;s game text (they are split 50/50) they get to use it.  Some cards a recycled, some get trashed after one use.  You have enough action rounds so that you have 1 extra card that you carry over to the next round.  You also can ditch an especially bad card to the "space race" every turn.  A lot of the game is based on managing crap hands and timing your "opponent" cards so they minimum impact.  As overall turns progress the mid and late war cards are added to deck, but by holding (or playing) cards you make it likely for them to not be seen/ be seen more.  <br />
<br />
Points are used to add influence to a county (each has a target #), if you have influence = target # you control.  They also can be used to reduce opponent&#39;s influence or agressively as an outright coup attempt.  Reducing influence can&#39;t hurt you but you never gain any there.  Coups let you gain influence but at a greater risk.<br />
<br />
Scoring cards pop up for regions (like continents in risk) and MUST be played.  <br />
<br />
Scoring track is +/- 20 pts... if either side gets to 20 game over.  <br />
<br />
It&#39;s a really nice game that takes a few time to get better at.  Knowing the cards really helps but ultimately it&#39;s a game of guessing your opponent&#39;s goals and thwarting them.  I think if I hadn&#39;t been so reckless the other night (just hoping for super cards to bail me out of trouble) I might have had more success. <br><BR><font size=1>12:11 12-05-2007</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Patrick M. S</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF' ><font class="bfont">Yeah, I&#39;ve never played before (neither has anyone else here) so a detailed game session wouldn&#39;t help. But yeah, if you wanna give an overview that would be great. Mostly, I&#39;m interested in knowing what you think works well with the game, what you find fun, etc. Basically, just review the game :)<br />
<br />
How long does it take? <br />
<br />
oh man, I can&#39;t wait to try it out.  <br><BR><font size=1>08:57 12-05-2007</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#CCCCCC>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><font class="bfont"><B>Shewski</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#CCCCCC' ><font class="bfont">Yeah, I;ve played about 8 times by now.<br />
<br />
