<br />
Power Grid has surprisingly become better and better and I&#39;m pushing it up the charts from my 4th favourite to my 2nd favourite. US, France, Germany and Italy maps are all great. There are 2 other expansions. One of them is good, the other is AWFUL. But yeah, I do like the game. I don&#39;t play with a calculator anymore and it&#39;s better. <br />
<br />
Tigris and Euphrates is still really good but I&#39;ve dropped it down to my 3rd favourite (pretty much tied with Caylus for 3rd). It&#39;s annoying that you can only play 4. And MAN is a 4 player game ever tight and intense. Still a great game but not as strong as those other two. <br />
<br />
Caylus is so ridiculously deep that it turns off too many players. The ones that do like it (surprisingly, my sister) are awesome cuz then I get to play it. But most of the time no one ever &#39;feels&#39; like playing Caylus or Tigris and Euphrates cuz they require alot of focus. <br />
<br />
So that&#39;s mainly why I think Puerto Rico and Power Grid, to a lessor extent, are the best. They are fun and everyone always feels like playing them.<br />
<br />
El Grande is right behind in 4th or 5th and I&#39;ve got samurai right up there with Battlelore so far. Pretty good but the 4-player cap is annoying.  <br><BR><font size=1>19:54 11-26-2007</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Patrick M. S</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF' ><font class="bfont">next stop for you... Puerto Rico <br><BR><font size=1>18:41 11-23-2007</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#CCCCCC>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><font class="bfont"><B>sithborg279</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#CCCCCC' ><font class="bfont">I am not giving up my addiction to Risk.  Got 3 Risks on my Christmas list.  But Settlers was great fun. <br><BR><font size=1>18:18 11-23-2007</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Patrick M. S</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF' ><font class="bfont">yeah, it wakes you up to a whole other world of board games. No more Risk :) <br><BR><font size=1>08:32 11-23-2007</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#CCCCCC>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><font class="bfont"><B>sithborg279</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#CCCCCC' ><font class="bfont">So I just had my first games of Settlers of Cataan.  Wow.  Just wow. <br><BR><font size=1>20:46 11-22-2007</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Patrick M. S</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF' ><font class="bfont">yeah, playing the power 4&#39;s early is near suicide I think. Sara continously nails me with figure exchange. I think they&#39;re better to slam down later on. But they are nice at locking up a region that you want to play in by yourself.  <br><BR><fo